x4freetext: THIN CIRCULAL FOILS OF 99.46 PER CENT 205-TL /0.54
PER CENT 203-TE/ WERE FABRICATED BY PRESSING IN AN
APPROPRIATE MOLD. THE THICKNESS VARIED FROM 630 TO
296 MILLIGRAMM/CM**2.THE THINNEST FOILS WERE USED IN
THE ENERGY REGION OF 40 TO 50 MEV TO OBTAIN MORE
DETAIL ON THE EXCITATION FUNCTION. A STACK OF
TWELVE FOILS WAS EXPOSED TO AN APPROXIMATELY 0.25
MUA BEAM OF 60 MEV PROTONS 1 HOUR. THE ENERGY OF
PROTON BEAM EXITING FROM THE TARGET WAS ABOUT 34 MEV.
